1. Injector records new news for publication
2. Executor receives notification from Kafka to store metadata in its local database
3. Saves metadata in its local database
4. Executor receives job request. Publish a news
5. Retrieves news metadata for publication
5.1 Fetch the metadata from the cache
5.2 Fetch the metadata from the local database
5.3 Fetch the metadata from the Injector Service Endpoint
6. Retrieves the original image of the news
7. Gets the main application to do the job. (A python script)
8. Runs the job and stores the result in the local database
9. Publish the job result in Kafka
